Package: linktaxa
Type: Package
Title: Link two related but not necessarily identical species lists
Version: 0.1-2
Date: 2013-12-06
Author: Roland Kaiser
Maintainer: Roland Kaiser <kardinal.eros@gmail.com>
Depends: R (>= 3.0.1), stringdist
Suggests: pbapply
Description: A package to link two related but not necessarily identical scientific species lists. The main function takes two character vectors of scientific taxon names and performs an exhaustive search for possible analogs. The package further provides tools to accommodate various tasks on species names.
License: GPL (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyLoad: yes
LazyData: yes
Collate: isWhat.R
         stripWhat.R
         dropIntraspecific.R
         expandSensuStricto.R
         asSensuStricto.R
         addSensuStricto.R
         subHybrid.R
         seekTaxon.R
         judgePenalty.R
         zeroPenalty.R
         relaxPenalty.R
         compareGenus.R
         queuePenalty.R
         linktaxa.R
         split.R
         prune.R
         abbreviate.R
         tplFamily.R

